<br>
They left their mark by their children, each race a creation of their own.<br>
<br>
As they designed, created, and made children that suited their own needs, and that repesented what they were, and how they felt about Norrath. Some even stole the works of others and &quot;perfected&quot; upon this form. Some of the children evolved on their own to entirely different forms. However, they began to realize a problem in all of their works.<br>
<br>
These beings were soulless hulks. They had no soul, they were just constructs of flesh and bone, created differently from one another. They could not properly represent them because without a soul they didn't even diserve to live. It was then when they realized that the nameless had another creation.<br>
<br>
Souls. Millions of spirits created by this enity, each with their own feelings, their true selves in their true forms. Some shined differently then others, some were bigger, some were smaller, each were infused with that which seperated one soul from another. Personality. Desire. Will. Morality. Loyality, and other traits<br>
<br>
These 5 traits at varing levels. Some had alot of Desire and Will but had a lack of Loyality. Some had high levels of Morality, but no desire or will. But they had Plenty of Loyality. The latter 4 is what creates the 5th, the personality. Their are other traits as well, and as the Gods looked over the pools of millions of souls that had been created.. they saw the way to make their children complete.<br>
<br>
They began to pick and choose which souls were suited to follow them, and be one of their own children. These souls were placed in the bodies and gave them life. The Gods also asigned certian skills to each soul, skills that best suited their personalities. <br>
<br>
For example, Innoruuk chose souls that were hateful. Tormented. Ones that could serve and be within hatred, and be loyal to him without crossing the barrier and loving him like a father. These weren't his only specifications, for one cannot truly know all of the specifications the gods place upon people. He placed those that had these types of souls into his children.. the Luggalds and the Tier'dal.<br>
<br>
Mithanel Marr chose those with the will to fight for a cause, with the Honor to protect the weak and destroy the vile in this world. He chose valours souls with high morality to be apart of his children.. The Barbarians, and the Froglocks.<br>
<br>
Solusek Ro chose those souls who wished power among anything else. He only allowed them to be casters, for that is what Ro believed the only true path to power to be. Solusek Ro has no true children upon Norrath, for he sprinkled his souls among most of the races of Norrath. We will discuss this a bit later on.<br>
<br>
The Gods sprinkled the souls upon their unique creations first. Cazic Thule to the Iksar, and Trolls Veeshan to the Dragons, Wurms, Drakes, and Wyverns, Tunare to the Fay and Elves.. and so on and so forth.<br>
<br>
These beings then truly became their children. They are the First Children, or the Children to be short.<br>
<br>
The Gods then realized that the First Children could not take up ALL of the souls.. This is where the conflict begins. This is where the comprimizes lie.<br>
<br>
In wake of this realization, they becan to spread their &quot;lesser&quot; sprits out into other peoples creations, or the evolution of their creations. They did not cross over too far however, wanting to only ensure that even these lesser souls got a suitable body that would fit their needs. Rallos Zek would never toss a soul over to an Highelf, for they are not combat hearty enought for his needs.<br>
<br>
This is where the Childless gods can get their own fills in. They did not create a race upon Norrath, so they tossed their souls into the races that had been created already. Solusek Ro found that the Erudites, an Evolution of Marrs Creation, The Tier'dal, and the Highelves were WELL suited for his magical power gaining needs.<br>
Rallos Zek saw that every race that had the ability to be a Warrior could create war. That is all he truly cares about, so he granted it such.<br>
Cazic Thule saw that the Erudites as well had a capasity to create fear. I dont know, maybe its something to do with the head.<br>
Everyone saw that the Evolution of Marrs creation, the Humans, could do just about anything. They got infused with alot of souls from the gods that were not of their creators.<br>
Bristlebane, being the ass that he is, throught it would be funny to have a twisted creation such as the Tier'dal be able to pull his worthless pranks, so he sent some souls there as well.<br>
<br>
These souls are known as the Second Children, or for short, the Followers.<br>
<br>
First Children or Second Children, or the Children and the Followers get asigned classes in the same way..<br>
<br>
The Gods assigned classes upon the children. From Bard to Warrior, they asigned each soul with a class that suited them best. Rallos Zek perfers and asignes martial classes, while the Tranquil perfers and asigns the classes of Monk and Paladin, usually. Ro perfers Wizardry, Karana perfers Druids.. some gods like Veeshan perfer none, and just asign upon how the soul appears to them.<br>
<br>
And when all was said and done, their were the souls that remained untouched by the gods.<br>
These souls were unworthy of any of the gods blessings to be a First or even a Second Children. Some of the Gods scorned them. Some of the Gods took pity upon them. Some of the Gods tossed them into bodies just to be malious and give them lives of torment to be weak. Some of the gods did this just so they could one day accept their teachings..<br>
<br>
But the Major ones who found use of these souls were the Demi Gods. Granted, they got some of their fill from the souls already touched from the gods, but they also had souls of their own. Terris Thule, Morrell Thule, Saryrn and the like. <br>
<br>
They are still Second Children if they follow a Demi God. <br>
<br>
For those that even the Demi Gods did not touch..<br>
<br>
They are the final Children. The Third Children who just fall into the world without the gods blessings.<br>
<br>
For short, we just call them.<br>
<br>
Agnostics. Faithless. Most of them are Vah Shir. They sprinkle across all of the races, some chose for themselves what race to be. I know not the creator of the Vah Shir, but I personally believe them to be evolved from the Kerrans. Their god must not like them much. These bastard children among all of the races. Cazic Thule faught vigously to protect his Iksars from these weak, bastard sprits. For you will not find an Agnostic Iksar.. I assume some of the other gods did the same.<br>
<br>
These sprits went to which bodies they throught suited them best. They made their own choice. Where ever they were allowed they went. The Vah Shir allowed them the most. Even if they were rejected by the gods, they went anyhow and found cracks to fill bodies just to be alive. Such is the desire of the soul.<br>
<br>
Once your soul fills a body and becomes alive, you forget all that has happened before you filled the body. Its like passing throught a viel which tears your memories.<br>
<br>
This is how we came to be.<br>
<br>
Children of the Gods.<br>
Followers of the Gods.<br>
And the rejects of the Gods. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=125476" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.studioeternity.com/EverquestFV/Shinsig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
