<br>
But more then likely, upon your 55th level of power, you will not stay in this life. You will leave, joining a lightbringer house and becomming docile. You will betray your own soul and become soft, and you will assist the light in gaining power.<br>
<br>
How can this happen? The answer is simple. While a soul may show traits of what the Dark Gods need, it is not always a lock that these souls will follow this their entire lives. These are the Fourth Children. (Or the Fallen Children.) They are below the agnostic, for they had the gift of being a First or Second child, but tossed it away because of their own weakness.<br>
<br>
They can reclaim such if they return and repent to their Father or Mother diety. Or they can die to the hands of the Children and the Followers.. the First and Second Children.<br>
<br>
The line for this is drawn at the Guild. Joining a Lightbringer guild implies alliance to the light, except in certian circumstances which has been organized in operations by the First Children. (For example, Ven'Sho's spy network.). Such should be approved by the First Children and the Followers before it being done, or you have become a Fourth Children.<br>
<br>
Their are also offences that do not involve guilds. Innoruuk didnt allow Tunare sponcered souls within his children. A Tier'dal or Luggald following Tunare is a Fourth Children. Understand? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=125476" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.studioeternity.com/EverquestFV/Shinsig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
