<br>
Shintou, I have looked long and hard into the history of the Vah Shir, and before them the Kerrans.<br>
<br>
I believe the young iksar is right.<br>
<br>
Should the Kerrans have evolved...well, they evolved from other cats upon Norrath.  And the Nameless formed Norrath along with everything on it.  Then it formed the gods, and gods formed their children.  And so on.<br>
<br>
Cats come from the Nameless, and therefore Kerrans were ultimately created from the Nameless.<br>
<br>
The Nameless is creation, pure and simple.<br>
<br>
It can be neither light nor dark.  It just is.<br>
<br>
Kerrans and Vah Shir hold to the tradition of the spirits.  They are not god-touched.  They do not fit into your theory, and they never will.  Vah Shir, and Kerrans, are the ultimate embodiments of free will, as created by the Nameless.  They can be whatever the spirits they follow bid them to be.<br>
<br>
They, of all the races, are truly agnostic.  And they are the ones who are most free to choose...light or dark.<br>
<br>
You will not like this, because it will force you to accept the Vah on the basis of their actions alone.  So continue to dig.  But you too will run into what I did.<br>
<br>
The Nameless.<br>
